        "id": 268171,
        "name": "Daniel Azuelos",
        "username": "Alias_duel_zone",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/alias_duel_zone/{size}/7470_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-05-18T17:21:57.693Z",
        "cooked": "<p>As a security and system engineer, I spend my life typing<br>\ntext files. Then I am used to the [return] key as a normal character<br>\nI use all the time. In fact on each line of text I type.<br>\nOn iOS, the [return] behaves as a standard [return] key, as expected<br>\nwith any usual keyboard.</p>\n<p>On MacOS, the [return] key is a function key, and immediatly<br>\nsend the message at the 1st line.<br>\nThus I always send stupid truncated messages every time I start<br>\nagain using Signal on my Mac, and I have to delete the sent<br>\nmessage immediatly and switch to a vi window to type at full<br>\nspeed the message I want to send and then copy-paste it from <code>vi</code><br>\nto Signal. Which is rather a very slow work flow.</p>\n<p>Is it possible to remove this function of the [return] key so as to<br>\navoid this repeated error and waste ot time to work around this<br>\ntrap of an unwanted function?</p>\n<p>Is it possible to remove this function with the <code>defaults</code> command?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
        "updated_at": "2025-05-18T20:04:35.376Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
