        "created_at": "2025-07-27T16:54:15.627Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thank you. I had hard time to understand your receipe because<br>\nthe chevron button is not displayed by default. I discovered it is<br>\ndisplayed only when passing the cursor above the Message box.<br>\nThis is perfect, but I think it would be a great improvment not to<br>\nhide this chevron button.<br>\nAll in all,<br>\n<strong>thank you</strong> <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/pray/2.png?v=12\" title=\":pray:t2:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":pray:t2:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"><br>\nfor this huge performance improvment in my use of Signal.</p>\n<p>Do you think it would be a nice function to add a preference choice<br>\nto exchange the function of:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">    return          → return\n    ⌘ + return      → send the message\n</code></pre>",
